# Fire Newts
Fire Newts orginal hail from the elemental plane of fire. Because of this fact firenewts are wowed by the most mundane of things found on the material plane. For instance firenewts throw outrageously large parties every night as they are unused to the idea of a nighttime.
Firenewts are about the size of a small human. They appear like lizardfolk with simpler faces and larger, dark-colored eyes. Their speckled, smooth skin appear eel-like and bears the color of flames. Firenewt colors have increasing rarity from red to yellow to white to blue. Even more rare are purple newts and above that green newts. Solid colored newts are very rare. There are not any known solid purple or green newts. Firenewts have long feet, giving them the appearance of "reversed knees".

Despite some misconceptions, firenewts are not infact releated to lizards and are instead more related to amphibians.

Firenewts require a source of magma in order to breed. When they do they deposit their clutch of eggs and leave their young to fend for themselves, because of this reason, Firenewts are far more communal seeing all newts as their family. 

Firenewts are known to carry around the ingredients to make an alchemical concoction made from mineral salts, sulfur and oil which they turn into a paste and chew as a habit to aid in their spitting of flames and warms them internally when away from a heat source or home. Firenewts have a great love of Alcohol, cheese and shiny materials such as gemstones. They have an especially large love of items that are green and purple. 


### Firenewt Traits


***Ability Score Increase:*** Your Constitution score increases by 2 and your Dexterity score increases by 1.

***Age:*** Firenewts can live an upwards of 100 or so years and mature around the age of 3.

***Alignment:*** Firenewts enjoy a chaotic lifestyle and thus they tend to dwell inside Chaotic allignments. 

***Size:*** Firenewts are about the size of a small human and range between 4-5ft tall and weigh around 90-110 lbs. Your size category is medium.   

***Speed:*** Your base walking speed is 30 feet.

***Favour The Heat:*** You're resistant to fire damage.

***Cold Aversion:*** You have disadvantage on attack rolls and on Intelligence (Investigation) checks that rely on sight when you are in a cold enviroment. 

***Spit Fire:*** You can spit fire at a creature within 10 feet of you as an bonus action. The creature must make a DC saving throw which equals 8 + your Constitution modifier + your proficiency bonus. A creature takes 2d8 fire damage on a failed save, and no damage on a successful one. The damage increases to 3d8 at 6th level, 4d8 at 11th level, and 5d8 at 16th level.

After you use this ability, you can’t use it again until you complete a short Rest.


***Jewelers Mastery:*** You gain proficiency with Jewelery Kits.

***Languages:*** You speak and write Common and can choose either Draconic or Ignan as an additional language.

***Names:*** Firenewts tend to favor X's



***Example Names:*** Ixenox, Ferix, Nixl'a


