# Water Newts
Waternewts are a race native to the plane of water. Waternewts constantly work torwards a deeper understanding of realty and what causes events to occur, they have dubbed this transcendent force "the current" and believe that this phenomenon is the reason behind every occcurance. Waternewts believe that nothing is above the force of the current, and even the dieties bend to this will. 

For many Waternewts, they establish a goal to seek early on in their lives, a project that they refer to as their Opus. Waternewts will spend nearly their entire lives working on their Opus, this project can range from attempting to uncover an artifact to creating the greatest flower garden ever made. In waternewt culture in order to ascend to the afterlife and have eternal happiness they complete this project.

The process by which a waternewt picks their Opus is largely out of their control, A waternewts Opus comes to them early on via a dream, a sign, or some other third party source. This event is believed by many waternewts to be predetermined and made aware to them by their races latent divination talents. Newts who don't recieve such a goal are considered abandoned by the "the current" and are cast out from society.

Waternewt cities are a confusing blend of canals, tunnels, and wide open spaces that randomly split between underwater spaces and above spaces making naviagting them difficult for those who are unable to breath underwater, waternewt currency is based on trade bars rather then gold.


<img 
  src='https://i.pinimg.com/originals/98/89/74/988974dfd2e785d3a6c5b1749157ef22.png' 
  style='position:absolute; top:100px; right:-157px; 	width:600px;mix-blend-mode:multiply'/>



### Waternewt Traits

***Ability Score Increase:*** Your Wisdom score increases by 2 and your Constitution score increases by 1.

***Age:*** Waternewts can live an upwards of 100 or so years and mature around the age of 3.

***Alignment:*** Waternewts tend to be more relaxed and willing to follow established rules and thus they tend to dwell inside lawful allignments. 

***The currents wake:*** Your deep understanding of the underlying force that influences everything grants you minor hints of the future. When you roll initiative, you can choose to either add or subtract 5 to the roll. This must be done before any actions in combat are taken. You can do this once per short rest.

***Size:*** Waternewts are about the size of a human and range between 5 and 5 and half feet tall and weigh around 100-130 lbs. Your size category is medium.     

***Speed:*** Your base walking speed is 30 feet and your swim speed is 30 feet.

***Aquatic Affinity:*** You're build allows you great mobility while swimming granting you a swim speed of 30 feet, furthermore you can breath both air and water.

***Common Water:*** Using gestures and sounds, you can communicate simple ideas with any beast that has an innate swimming speed.

***Languages:*** You speak and write Common and can choose either Aquan or Deep Speech as a second language.

***Names:*** Waternewt names tend to be poetic in nature.

***Example Names:*** Last drop of the water, A murky abyss, Water turnt to Ice.

