<h1 style="font-size:4vw">Subclasses</h1>

## Barbarian Path: Path of the Battlerager (Rework)

### Battlerager Armor
When you choose this path at 3rd level, you gain the ability to use spiked armor as a weapon.



|Name | Cost | Armor Class | Weight| Type |
|:---:|:---:|:---|:---:|
| Spiked Armor | 75 gp | 14 + Dex modifier (max 2)| 10 | Medium|

When you are wearing spiked armor, and holding nothing in your hands, or using a shield, you can use it as a weapon that has the heavy and two-handed properties. Additionally, while you are “wielding” the armor, you can still grapple other creatures. Magical spiked armor adds the magical bonus to AC to its attack rolls and damage rolls and counts as magical for the purposes for overcoming resistances and immunities.

The damage dice of the Spiked Armor starts at 1d6 and increases as you gain levels in this subclass.
The damage dice changes to 1d8 at 6th level, 1d10 at 10th level, and 1d12 at 14th level.


Additionally, when you are grappling a creature, you can make an attack using your Spiked Armor as a bonus action against the grappled creature


### Reckless Abandon
Beginning at 6th level, when you use Reckless Attack while raging, you also gain temporary hit points equal to your Constitution modifier (minimum of 1). They vanish if any of them are left when your rage ends.

Additionally, the damage dice of your spiked armor changes to 1d8


### Battlerager Charge
Beginning at 10th level, you can take the Dash action as a bonus action while you are raging. If you dash as a bonus action and attack a creature on the same turn, you can attempt to grapple the creature one time for free.

Additionally, the damage dice of your spiked armor changes to 1d10


### Spiked Retribution
Starting at 14th level, when a creature within 5 feet of you hits you with a melee attack, the attacker takes 1d12 piercing damage if you are raging, aren't incapacitated, and are wearing spiked armor. If you are wearing magical spiked armor, this damage counts as magical, but you do not add any extra damage to the effect.

Additionally, the damage dice of your spiked armor changes to 1d12

