## Fighter - Martial Archetype: Olympian

### Peak Physical Condition
Starting at 3rd level you gain proficency in in athletics if you don't already have it, additionaly whenever you make Strength(Atletics) check, you gain a bonus to the check equal to your Dexterity modifier and you count as one size larger when determining your carrying capacity and the weight you can push, drag, or lift.
### Wrestling
At 3rd level you become an expert at grappling and manoeuvring foes you have grappled. You gain ability to attempt to grapple creature within your reach as a bonus action. Additionally you can perform special Wrestling Techniques on target you are grappling fueled by Wrestling Dice. 
___
**Wrestling Dice.** You have four wrestling dice, which are d8s. A wrestling die is expended when you use it. You regain all of your expended wrestling dice when you finish a short or long rest.
You gain another wrestling die at 7th level and one more at 15th level.
___
**Unarmed combat.** You can roll your d8 in place of the normal damage of your unarmed strike. This damage grows with your wrestling dice.
___
**Wrestling techniques.** As a bonus action you can expend one wrestling die and perfom one of the following wrestling techniques on target you are grappling. Save DC for them is equal to 8 + Your Strength Modifier + Your Proficiency Modifier
___

Slam: As a bonus action you can slam a creature against the ground. Target takes bludgeoning damage equal to your wrestling die and have to make Strength saving throw. On a failure target is knocked prone.
___
Choke: As a bonus action you can attempt to squeeze or choke the creature you are grappling. Target takes bludgeoning damage equal to your wrestling die and have to make Constitution saving throw. Targets that don't need to breath automatically pass save. On a failure target is suffucating and has disadvantage on all ability checks and attack rolls until the end of your next turn. Effect ends if you break your grapple.
___
Throw: As a bonus action you can throw the creature you are grappling with all your might. Target that is one size category larger than you or smaller takes bludgeoning damage equal to your wrestling die and have to make Dexterity saving throw. On a failure you can throw target up to 10 ft. in a horizontal direction of your choice. If target hits another creature or object they both take bludgeoning damage equal to your wrestling die.
<br>
<br>
<br>
### Might of Olympus
Starting at 7th level your unarmed attacks and wrestling dice damage count as magical for the purpose of overcoming resistance and immunity to nonmagical attacks and damage.
### Additional Wrestling Die
Starting at 7th level you gain additional Wrestling Die.
### Titan's Grip
Starting at 10th level, you gain ability to grapple and shove creatures 2 size categories larger than you.
### Improved Wrestling (d10)
Starting at 10th level, your wrestling dice turn into d10s.
### Endurance to hold the world
At 15th level, whenever you use Second Wind feature you gain resistance to bludgeoning, piercing and slashing damage until the end of your next turn. Additionaly, when you roll initiative and have no wrestling dice remaining, you regain 1 wrestling die.
### Additional Wrestling Die
Starting at 15th level you gain additional Wrestling Die.
### Performance of Great labor.
At 18th level, you gain ability to grapple and shove creatures 3 size categories larger than you.
### Improved Wrestling (d12)
Starting at 18th level, your wrestling dice turn into d12s.

