## Roguish Archetype: Brigand

Rogues of this archetype usually are skilled self-tought warriors that excel in fighting using many tricks and dirty moves in their arsenal. They never fight fair and always seek any advantage they can utilize to earn victory.

### Highwayman
When you choose this archetype at 3rd level you develop your own fighting style that involves clean strikes at weak points where it will hurt most. You gain proficency with medium armor and you are now profient in intimidation skill if you are not already proficient in it.
Pick one martial or simple melee weapon that doesn't have heavy or special property, unarmed strike or natural weapon. This weapon counts as finesse for you and you are proficient with it. 
You can change your highwayman weapon every time you level up. You gain another Highwayman Weapon at level 9
### Dirty Trick
Starting at 3rd level, as a bonus action you can try to distract one target within 5 ft. of you that you can see. Make Dexterity(Sleight of hand) check contested by target's Wisdom(perception) check. You must have free hand to use this feature. If you succeed, you have advantage on all your attack against this target and it have
disadvantage on attacks against you until the end of your next turn. You can use this feature number of times equal to your Proficiency Bonus. You regain all uses after finishing long rest.
___
You also gain ability to throw off balance your opponents after sucessfuly distracting them. Once per turn, if you hit target that is effected by your Dirty Trick feature with melee weapon attack, you can attempt to shove it prone as a bonus action. While shoving this way you can use Dexterity(Sleight of hands) skill instead of Strength(Athletics)(Whatever is higher)
### Intimidate
Starting at 9th level, you learn how to instil great fear in your foes or any poor souls that decided to cross your pass. As an action choose one creature within 30 ft. that you can see, can understand your speech and is able to see you. Make Charisma(Intimidation) check contested by target's Wisdom(Insight) check. On a success target is frightened of you for 1 minute or until it takes any damage.
### Tough as nails
Starting at 13th level, whenever you use Uncanny Dodge feature you also reduce damage by number equal to your proficiency bonus + Dexterity modifier after halving it.
### Prey on weak
Starting at 17th level, whenever you hit creature that is restrained, frightened, blinded or incapacitated with melee attack your sneak attack damage is increased by 3d6.

