<h1 style="font-size:5vw">Spells</h1>
	
### Assasin's Mark
*transmuatation cantrip*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 bonus action
- **Range:** 30 ft
- **Components:** V, S
- **Duration:** Permanent
- **Classes:** Warlock, Wizard

___
When cast upon a creature killed by you within a minute of its death, assasins mark reshapes the wound in a way that unmistakably identifies you as the killer.
	
You select the form this mark will take when you learn the spell, and you can't change it later except through exceptional magic such as the wish spell.

No two creatures can share the same assasin's mark.

	<br> 

### Iron fist 
*transmutation cantrip*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 bonus action
- **Range:** Self 
- **Components:** V, S
- **Duration:** Instantaneous
- **Classes:** Artificer, Cleric, Wizard

---
**Description:** The rising popularity of, what have been referred to as"fist wizards", has led to the creation of new magic to suit this style of fighting. 
Metal coats the skin of the caster as they begin casting, and they can then choose to make a special unarmed strike attack against a creature within 5ft. On a hit, the target takes 1d6 bludgeoning damage (recieving no bonus from strength or casting modifier, just to be in line with other cantrips) as the steely hide of the caster's fist slams into them.

---
The caster's skin remains hard for a few seconds as a side effect to the casting. Hit or miss, the user gains temporary hit points equal to their spellcasting ability modifier until the beginning of their next turn. The quantity of temporary hit points gained cannot be increased by any means. However, they have disadvantage on Dexterity Saving Throws and their movement speed is reduced by 5ft. 

---
The spell's damage increases by 1d6 and the temporary hit points granted increase by your spellcasting ability modifier when you reach 5th level (2d6 and 2 times spellcasting ability modifier THP), 11th level (3d6 and 3 times spellcasting ability modifier THP), and 17th level (4d6 and 4 times spellcasting ability modifier THP).
	

