### Devils of the Dunes
*3rd-level conjuration*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 10 feet
- **Components:** V,S,M (3 gemstones worth 50g each)
- **Duration:** 1 minute, concentration
- **Classes:** Wizard

Summon 1 dust mephit as part of the action to cast this spell, as a bonus action on subsequent turns an additional mephit can be summoned up to a maximum of 3 at once. If the spell ends the mephits die. The colour of the gems used determines the eye colour of the mephits.

___
**At higher levels.** when you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher the maximum amount of mephits summoned at once increases by 1 for each slot level above 3rd.
	
<div class='descriptive'>
The above spell is heretical. Being caught using it will incur consequences from the Church of Eli if the caster is found out.
</div>
	
### Elder Sign
___
*3rd-level abjuration*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 hour
- **Range**: Touch
- **Components**: V, S, M (special ink or tools worth 500 gp,
which the spell consumes), D (up to 5 feet across, on
object touched)
- **Duration:** Until Dispelled
- **Classes**: Wizards, Sorcerers
- **Subclasses**: Cleric (Arcana Domain), Warlock (Pact of the Undying)
___
You create an Elder Sign on an object you touch. The Elder
Sign is immune to the damage, spells, and abilities from
any CR 20+ aberrations, or creatures bound to
their service. These creatures can’t touch or pass through
an object with the Elder Sign. Generally, an Elder Sign is
destroyed after being within 30 feet of a CR 20+ aberration
for more than 5 continuous rounds. Note that since only
the Elder Sign itself has immunity to various alien horrors,
its protection can be unreliable. For example, a shield with
the Elder Sign drawn on it would not be affected by a Great
Old One’s attack, but the monster could still strike the bearer
if it avoids striking the shield (and thus the bearer’s AC is
not any higher than it would be with an unmarked shield).
Engraving the sign upon a door or on an archway prevents
such creatures from passing through the portal.

___
**At Higher Levels.** When you cast this spell using a spell
slot of 4th level or higher, you can create an Elder Sign
with a radius of up to 5 feet, plus 5 feet per level of the
spell slot above 3rd.

	<br>
	
### Gallow tree
*4th-level conjuration (ritual)*
___
- **Casting time:** 1 action
- **Range**: Touch
- **Components:** V, S
- **Duration:** 1 week
- **Classes:** Warlock, Wizard


One creature you can see must make a wisdom saving throw. If it fails, it becomes mystically linked to a structure or tree of your choosing on the same plane. If the creature dies during the duration of the spell, its body is instantly teleported to the structure or tree and bound to it by stout ropes.

<div class='descriptive'>
The above spell is heretical. Being caught using it will incur consequences from the Church of Eli if the caster is found out.
</div>
	
### Skeletal Deliquesce 
*8th-level transmutation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action 
- **Range:** 60 ft
- **Components:** V, S, M (a cube of gelatin)
- **Duration:** Instantaneous 
- **Classes**: Wizards, Sorcerers

Description: You attempt to reduce a flesh-and-blood creature you can see within range to a quivering mass of meat by removing its skeleton. The target must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or have its skeleton vanish, falling prone and becoming unable to stand up. A creature with its skeleton so vanished has its speed reduced to 10 feet and can not cast spells, attack, or perform any action that requires the use of its limbs. On each of its turns, the target can use an action to attempt a DC 16 Constitution ability check, restoring its skeleton on a success and ending the effect.
	

### Mori Memento
*4th-level divination*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 minute
- **Range:** Touch
- **Components:** V,S,M (a strand of hair or drop of blood from the target)
- **Duration:** instantaneous
- **Classes**: Cleric, Wizard
___
You target a willing creature and learn what fate will befall it near death. Roll all results for death saves as if it was just reduced to 0 hit points. 
___
For the next 24 hours if target creature must make death saves, it will use the rolled results per round, in order that they received them. If at the time of actually dying, the creature was told his death saves and is under the effects of something that would help or hinder that roll, simply make the addition/subtraction to the next predetermined roll or in the case that something gives advantage/disadvantage, roll a second dice and take the appropriate number. This spell has no effect on creatures that lack the ability to make death saves.


